114
00:05:51,797 --> 00:05:56,381
So to start off, you can break down player skills being tested in a game into a lot of different buckets.

115
00:05:56,461 --> 00:06:01,465
Things like good decision making, good team communication, fast reflexes, and so forth.

116
00:06:02,566 --> 00:06:05,668
Now one of the biggest differences between highly skilled and normal skilled players

117
00:06:06,028 --> 00:06:07,349
comes in execution difficulty.

118
00:06:08,330 --> 00:06:12,513
As developers, we sometimes balance, often balance, the power of an ability

119
00:06:12,754 --> 00:06:14,715
with it being difficult for a player to pull off.

120
00:06:15,296 --> 00:06:19,319
So this is a basic skill shot, League of Legends is full of them, rather than...

121
00:06:20,451 --> 00:06:24,632
clicking on the enemy target with your mouse and then just hitting a button that will always hit them,

122
00:06:24,932 --> 00:06:28,794
you have to line up the attack and take into consideration things like, you know,

123
00:06:28,874 --> 00:06:31,354
leading them, predicting where the enemy's going to be, and so forth.

124
00:06:35,676 --> 00:06:40,937
But it's not just skill shots. Anything involving timing or multitasking or often just the speed of clicking,

125
00:06:40,957 --> 00:06:43,978
you know, APM, is much easier for highly skilled players.

126
00:06:45,615 --> 00:06:48,938
Some of the ultimates in League of Legends, the R ability, are channeled.

127
00:06:49,218 --> 00:06:52,981
And a channeled ability, you can think of the champion as like winding up, casting a spell.

128
00:06:53,261 --> 00:06:57,765
And during that time, if they get interrupted, it either cancels a spell outright or it might have a diminished effect.

129
00:06:58,786 --> 00:07:01,849
This is Fiddlesticks, our evil, magical scarecrow.

130
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:07,314
He has an ult called Crowstorm where he summons a lot of crows, but he does have to channel it.

131
00:07:07,634 --> 00:07:08,795
And this is the kind of thing that...

132
00:07:09,803 --> 00:07:14,525
makes it a little harder to use at the pro level because, or even at highly skilled players,

133
00:07:14,585 --> 00:07:16,106
because it will get interrupted.

134
00:07:16,966 --> 00:07:18,907
You have to keep in mind when you're talking about these, you know,

135
00:07:19,508 --> 00:07:22,089
1% of skilled players,

136
00:07:22,469 --> 00:07:25,410
anything whose cost is easy to interrupt is going to be interrupted.

137
00:07:25,871 --> 00:07:28,912
And anything whose cost is hard to pull off, they will pull off.

138
00:07:32,308 --> 00:07:33,630
It's not just feats of dexterity, though.

139
00:07:34,210 --> 00:07:37,114
Skilled players understand the higher-level strategies of the game as well.

140
00:07:37,595 --> 00:07:39,577
They can pull from a lot of knowledge,

141
00:07:40,038 --> 00:07:43,442
including knowing strengths and weaknesses of champions almost reflexively.

