00:08:07,374 --> 00:08:09,615
So, going way back to my roots at the Age of Empires,

152
00:08:09,835 --> 00:08:12,516
this is one of the first balanced nemesis I ever faced.

153
00:08:13,417 --> 00:08:15,297
Two of the most powerful traits you can give

154
00:08:15,317 --> 00:08:19,379
a unit character champion are long range and fast movement.

155
00:08:20,099 --> 00:08:21,480
And the two together is amazing.

156
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,321
Cavalry archers were the bane of my existence

157
00:08:24,401 --> 00:08:25,181
on Age of Empires.

158
00:08:25,462 --> 00:08:27,362
There's a reason the Mongols were so effective with them.

159
00:08:28,583 --> 00:08:30,404
You run up, you shoot, you run away.

160
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:31,944
They're experts at kiting.

161
00:08:31,964 --> 00:08:34,245
It makes it very difficult for other units

162
00:08:34,285 --> 00:08:35,806
or other players to be able to catch up with them.

163
00:08:36,912 --> 00:08:42,576
This extends to League of Legends. We have champions like Vayne and Lucian who are highly mobile yet ranged.

164
00:08:43,217 --> 00:08:48,862
And skilled players who are great at micromanagement are going to be able to do a lot of damage with never having to take damage themselves.

165
00:08:52,536 --> 00:08:55,879
Now this is an interesting one. Most league players experience the game solo.

166
00:08:55,919 --> 00:08:59,062
We have matchmaking. We'll find you a team and we'll find you an enemy team.

167
00:08:59,802 --> 00:09:02,465
But organized play is a very different experience.

168
00:09:02,505 --> 00:09:04,867
And of course anything professional is organized play.

169
00:09:04,907 --> 00:09:07,549
These guys play together all the time. They have plays.

170
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,491
They can almost read each other's minds.

171
00:09:10,512 --> 00:09:13,514
You think of like a buddy cop movie where the two cops enter a building

172
00:09:13,534 --> 00:09:15,876
and they immediately know to cover each other's blind spots.

173
00:09:18,043 --> 00:09:23,766
Lowelow, on the other hand, because they don't have the guarantee that someone's going to help defend them,

174
00:09:24,626 --> 00:09:27,728
tend to gravitate more towards generalists.

175
00:09:27,748 --> 00:09:31,009
This cute critter here is Kog'Maw. He's a classic glass cannon.

176
00:09:31,049 --> 00:09:35,031
He can do a ton of damage at range, but if you get up in his face, he crumbles very quickly.

177
00:09:35,431 --> 00:09:40,813
And as you might imagine, it's difficult for players in solo queue to be able to effectively utilize him

178
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,294
because they just don't know that their team's going to be there backing them up.

179
00:09:47,813 --> 00:09:50,135
Highly skilled players are really good at manipulating your economy,

180
00:09:50,155 --> 00:09:54,738
and getting an economic advantage in any game can often be really powerful.

181
00:09:55,879 --> 00:09:58,021
In League of Legends, we see this as gold funneling.

182
00:09:58,481 --> 00:10:01,884
So basically, in League, you kill things, you get gold,

183
00:10:01,964 --> 00:10:03,966
use the gold to buy more items to get powerful.

184
00:10:04,006 --> 00:10:07,228
And the idea is that everyone kind of rises in power as the game goes on,

185
00:10:07,248 --> 00:10:08,990
and more skilled players rise a little faster.

186
00:10:09,951 --> 00:10:12,894
But skilled players, we see this definitely with pros,

187
00:10:13,295 --> 00:10:15,877
can kind of have a lot of the team avoid getting gold

188
00:10:15,897 --> 00:10:18,040
to make sure that one player gets a lot of gold early.

189
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,962
So they have this really powerful spike,

190
00:10:20,562 --> 00:10:22,184
and even though it's only one player on the team,

191
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:23,966
they can leverage that to get an advantage.

192
00:10:26,124 --> 00:10:30,227
In World of Warcraft, we would see this with the high-end guilds when they would raid,

193
00:10:30,267 --> 00:10:34,170
would do things like, we're going to pass all the gear to the main tank or to, you know,

194
00:10:34,190 --> 00:10:36,031
a really important DPS character.

195
00:10:36,471 --> 00:10:41,435
And this got to the point of running alt raids, where a group would run a raid,

196
00:10:41,735 --> 00:10:44,217
all the gear would go to one player while everyone else was on their alt,

197
00:10:44,237 --> 00:10:47,400
they'd switch to the next player and so on and so on, using different raid instances.

198
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,342
It's hard to stop, it's hard to design around that,

199
00:10:50,782 --> 00:10:54,925
but it makes balance very difficult for these high-end raiding guilds.

200
00:10:59,024 --> 00:10:59,964
AI-dependent power.

201
00:11:01,006 --> 00:11:02,487
We love to put turrets in our games.

