207
00:11:19,673 --> 00:11:21,515
If you think of the power as a pie chart,

208
00:11:21,935 --> 00:11:25,819
the AI part of that power takes up a big part of that pie chart. It doesn't really

209
00:11:25,899 --> 00:11:28,502
change depending on whether you're talking at lower or high skill level.

210
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:32,984
So as developers, we have to kind of choose where we're going to tune those turrets.

211
00:11:33,344 --> 00:11:35,965
And if we tune them to be very, very powerful at high end,

212
00:11:35,985 --> 00:11:37,966
they're just going to crush lower end players.

213
00:11:38,546 --> 00:11:40,587
On the other hand, if you do what most of us do and make them

214
00:11:40,927 --> 00:11:43,008
relatively reasonably fair at lower levels,

215
00:11:43,389 --> 00:11:45,670
at high levels, they're just not going to see them get much play.

216
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:54,301
Strong windowed power. This is one of those cases where as developers we often

217
00:11:54,641 --> 00:11:59,363
make the cost of like, yeah, we're going to give you a lot of power but it's going to last for a really, really short period of time.

218
00:12:00,683 --> 00:12:05,145
The more skilled players won't waste that time. Even if it's a really small window, they can get a lot out of that.

