00:26:31,769 --> 00:26:34,310
It can be a hard sell when you're trying to convince the

495
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:35,130
studio to hire.

496
00:26:35,410 --> 00:26:39,111
In this case, we need over 10 players to be able to play a

497
00:26:39,131 --> 00:26:39,851
10-player game.

498
00:26:40,252 --> 00:26:43,832
But it's worth it when you consider that the designers in

499
00:26:43,872 --> 00:26:46,813
QA who are probably in the trenches can't play the game

500
00:26:47,053 --> 00:26:47,653
all day long.

501
00:26:47,693 --> 00:26:49,974
They have to actually sit at the computer and make changes

502
00:26:50,034 --> 00:26:50,354
as well.

503
00:26:50,834 --> 00:26:53,275
So without someone playing the game constantly, you may only

504
00:26:53,315 --> 00:26:54,795
get two or three games in during the day.

505
00:26:56,207 --> 00:26:58,789
Again, I understand for a small studio or an indie dev,

506
00:26:58,809 --> 00:26:59,850
this isn't going to be feasible.

507
00:27:01,191 --> 00:27:03,853
And as a warning, high ELO players are going to suggest

508
00:27:03,893 --> 00:27:04,794
high ELO changes.

509
00:27:04,934 --> 00:27:06,716
You just have to keep that in mind when they're talking

510
00:27:06,756 --> 00:27:09,078
about, hey, I thought of a way to fix this that's probably

511
00:27:09,098 --> 00:27:12,120
going to fix it for them and not necessarily all the rest

512
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:12,760
of the skill tiers.

513
00:27:16,704 --> 00:27:20,106
I talked about how we had a focus team, and we focus on a

514
00:27:20,146 --> 00:27:22,508
target ELO, but we also have a focus target time.

515
00:27:23,707 --> 00:27:25,889
Just as with our professional game, ranked play in league

516
00:27:25,929 --> 00:27:26,749
follows a season.

517
00:27:27,690 --> 00:27:30,372
The ranked season turns on, players progress, and then at

518
00:27:30,412 --> 00:27:31,413
the end of the year it turns off.

519
00:27:32,654 --> 00:27:34,936
And we know that systemic changes, or even things like a

520
00:27:34,996 --> 00:27:38,338
new champion launch, we recently launched Camille.

